@node Introduction "What is MagicEditor?!"
@toc main
Introduction
------------

With MagicEditor you can finally write your messages with your favorite text
editor like Cygnus Editor.

@endnode


@node installation "Installing MagicEditor"
@toc main

Installation
------------

Just copy the whole MagicEditor directory to 'DOORS:' and add the following
line to your Editors.config

"MagicEditor" ^10000^1^Doors:MagicEditor/MagicEditor

Change yourself to this editor with a usereditor and make sure remote users
can't change to this editor!!

Now change the MagicEditor.config file to your likings.

@endnode

@node config " "
@toc main

;
;This is the command to run your ascii-editor
;if you put AUTO behind it the command will be
;runned at startup.
;
STARTEDITORCOMMAND  "C:BIN/CED t:message.tmp -sticky" AUTO

;
;The crossreply-header. Check for a list of the '%' cookies below.
;
CROSSREPLYHEADER                "** Cross-reply from '%A'"

;
;The editor will take this replyheader for default. Again, check below for
;a list of '%' cookies.
;
DEFAULTREPLYHEADER              "%F wrote a message to %T about '%S'"

;
;with this __ you can use a specific replyheader (instead of the default one)
;for a range of messagearea's. Use as much as REPLYHEADER lines as your
;memory permits.
;
REPLYHEADER          100-120    "%F wrote about '%S'"
REPLYHEADER          0,5-10,23  "Op %D schreeuwde %F iets waanzinnigs tegen mij over:"

;
;Defaultsignatures and signatures for specific message area's.
;
DEFAULTSIGNATURENORMAL              Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature
DEFAULTSIGNATUREHANDLE              Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature.handle
SIGNATURE           50-99           Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature.nla
SIGNATURE           15-25,300-400   Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature.fido
SIGNATURE           100-118,600-650 Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature.handle
SIGNATURE           700-800         Doors:MagicEditor/signatures/.signature.usenet

;
;Defaulttagline and taglines for specific message area's.
;
DEFAULTTAGLINE                      Doors:MagicEditor/taglines/MagicEditor.taglines
TAGLINE             109             Doors:MagicEditor/taglines/Pentiumtags
TAGLINE             0,50-81,100-118 Doors:MagicEditor/taglines/MagicEditor.taglines.nl

;
;Default charsets and charsets for specific message area's
;
DEFAULTCHARSET                 "LATIN-1 2"
CHARSET             25         "IBMPC 1"
CHARSET             52-100,150 "SWEDISH"

;*** List of '%' cookies for replyheaders ***
;
;    \n - newline
;
;    %F - the sender of the quoted message.
;    %f - the first name of the sender of the quoted message.
;    %n - the nodenumber of the sender of the quoted message.
;
;    %T - the recipient of the quoted message.
;    %t - the first name of the recipient of the quoted message.
;
;    %S - the subject of the quoted message.
;
;    %D - the date the quoted message was written, in MM-DDD-YY format.
;    %U - the time the quoted message was written, in HH:MM:SS format.
;
;    %A - the name of the messagearea the quoted message was written in.
;    %a - the tagname of the messagearea the quoted message was written in.

@endnode

@node How_To " "
@toc main

How to register
---------------

MagicEditor is a shareware program, this  means  you can try it out for free
but if you like it you must pay a shareware fee to the author (that's me).

When you register you'll get

 - A keyfile which will unlock MagicEditor and MagicFile(*) and any future
   'Magic' doors/utilities I will make.

(*) MagicFile is a fullscreen file-tagger/lister.  Check your local support
    board.


I have set the fee as following:

Dutch guys, CASH IN ENVELOPE   35,-    (35 Dutch guilders)

Other, CASH IN ENVELOPE        US$25,- (25 American dollars)

Other, BY EUROCHEQUE           45,-    (45 Dutch guilders, no other currenties!)


There is one more option, if you have some nice Magic, The Gathering
cards i might want to trade them for a keyfile. Contact me through the
Xenolink echo's, netmail or my @{"bbs" Link BBS}.

Fill in the registration.form you found in the archive and send it together
with the money to my address  (which you can find at the bottom of
registration.form).

When I have received the money I'll crash the key to your fidonet number,
if you don't have one you can download the key at my @{"bbs" Link BBS}.
@endnode
